To run this program:
Assemble: nasm -f elf32 main.asm
Link:     ld -m elf_i386 main.o
Execute:  ./a.out

nasm -f elf32 main.asm && ld -m elf_i386 main.o

This program allows the user to enter the size of their data and then enter their data
The program accepts integer inputs and stores the inputs as contiguous bytes of memory.
The program checks if the array is sorted in an ascending order.
If the array is not sorted then the quick sort algorithm is used to sort it.
After the array is sorted the program prompts the user to enter a search target and searches for the target using the binary search algorithm.
If the target is found, a message is printed to notify the user that the target was found and the index is displayed.
If the target was not found, a message is printed to notify the user that the target was not found.
Finally, a message is printed to notify the user that the program has ended and then the program exits.
